can be quite static,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"thus, you have to be quite careful to have a model work with dynamic inputs.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You cannot use reshape, or anything that can generate fixed tensor outputs from","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a fixed inputs.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ModelBuilder"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"T"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["Linux"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A model builder on the other hand doesn’t have that restriction. When input changes,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it simply calls the given builder closure to construct a new model. In such way,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you can continue to use reshape etc to assume fixed inputs and outputs, it will just"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"work for dynamic inputs. The newly built model will carry over stateful components"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(parameters) from the old models, thus, it doesn’t reset your training. This also means"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you need to make sure parameter shape won’t change when input changes, otherwise we"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will fatal."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/nnc\/modelbuilder"]}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/NNC/ModelBuilder/compile